class Solution {
    public int minOrAfterOperations(int[] nums, int k) {
        int ans = 0;
        int mask = 0;
        for (int b = 29; b >= 0; b--) {
            mask |= 1 << b;
            int cnt = 0; // 操作次数
            int and = -1; // -1 的二进制全为 1
            for (int x : nums) {
                and &= x & mask;
                if (and != 0) {
                    cnt++; // 合并 x，操作次数加一
                } else {
                    and = -1; // 准备合并下一段
                }
            }
            if (cnt > k) {
                ans |= 1 << b; // 答案的这个比特位必须是 1
                mask ^= 1 << b; // 后面不考虑这个比特位
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}

Explanation:
Here is the description of the completed code:
In the for loop, the variable b goes from 29 to 0, each time representing a specific bit. The variable mask is used to extract the bit from each element in the nums array. Then the variable and is used to perform the bitwise AND operation, the result is used to record the status of the bits that need to be merged. The cnt variable is used to count the number of merges that can be performed. The if branch is used to determine whether the number of merges that can be performed is greater than the current value of k. If it is greater than the current value of k, then it can be determined that in the next step, the specific bit of the merged result is 1. So you need to fill in the value of ans. The value of mask should be adjusted accordingly to avoid repeated merging.

